values.name: IndependentChannels
values.description-en: Channel n and channel n + 1 are independent.

values.name: ConnectedChannels
values.description-en: Channel n and channel n + 1 are connected.

enums.name: NI.FIU.Bus
enums.description-en: Selects which Bus is connected to the channel.

enums.name: NI.FIU.Load
enums.description-en: Determines if channel n is connected to load pin n.

values.name: NoLoad
values.description-en: The Load is not connected to channel n.

values.name: Load
values.description-en: The Load is connected to channel n.

interrupts.name: UpdateComplete
interrupts.description-en: Signals completion of the most recent Update operation

bitfields.name: UpdateDone
bitfields.description-en: When UpdateDone is '0', an update to the channels and/or buses is in progress.

bitfields.name: CycleDelays
bitfields.description-en: Number of 12.8 us cycles of delay to achieve around 2ms delay. Determines how long connection updates take to execute.

bitfields.name: FastCount
bitfields.description-en: Number of 12.8 us cycles of delay to achieve around 1ms delay. Used to determine digital filtering time for OverCurrentHigh and Bus OverCurrent Faults

bitfields.name: SlowCount
bitfields.description-en: Number of 6.55 ms cycles of delay to achieve around 1s delay. Used to determine digital filtering time for OverCurrentLow and OverTemperature faults.

bitfields.description-en: If '1', it means overcurrent was detected on bus A.

bitfields.name: BusB_OverCurrent
bitfields.description-en: If '1', it means overcurrent was detected on bus A.

bitfields.name: OvercurrentHigh
bitfields.description-en: If '1', it means overcurrent was detected on the channel corresponding to the bit position.

bitfields.name: OvercurrentLow
bitfields.description-en: If '1', it means overcurrent was detected on the channel corresponding to the bit position.

bitfields.name: OvertemperatureChannel
bitfields.description-en: If '1', it means over temperature was detected on the channel corresponding to the bit position.

bitfields.name: OvertemperatureDifferential
bitfields.description-en: If '1', it means over temperature was detected on the channel pair corresponding to the bit position.

bitfields.name: TempFaultVector
bitfields.description-en: If '1', it means over temperature was detected at the digital temperature sensor corresponding to the bit position.

bitfields.name: SlscInterfaceUnusedPin
bitfields.description-en: State of the unused SLSC Pin

bitfields.name: ClearWriteDuringUpdateError
bitfields.description-en: Write 1 to this bit to allow the module change the configuraiton. Alternatively you can reset the module.

bitfields.name: FlashHold
bitfields.description-en: Unused, this bit is ignored.

bitfields.name: FlashWriteProtect
bitfields.description-en: 0: Flash protected against write. 1: Flash available for write.

properties.name: NI.FIU.ModuleControllerVersion
properties.description-en: Read only Module Controller Version number
properties.documentation-en: The version is the timestamp, in hexadecimal format, of the time the Module Controller was compiled.

properties.name: NI.FIU.BoardFault
properties.description-en: True when there is any fault on the board

properties.name: NI.FIU.TemperatureSensor0
properties.description-en: Degrees Celsius of one of the board's 4 quadrant digital temperature sensors.

properties.name: NI.FIU.TemperatureSensor1
properties.description-en: Degrees Celsius of one of the board's 4 quadrant digital temperature sensors.

properties.name: NI.FIU.TemperatureSensor2
properties.description-en: Degrees Celsius of one of the board's 4 quadrant digital temperature sensors.

properties.name: NI.FIU.TemperatureSensor3
properties.description-en: Degrees Celsius of one of the board's 4 quadrant digital temperature sensors.

properties.name: NI.FIU.Calibration.Date
properties.description-en: Time, in seconds elapsed since 12:00 a.m., Friday, January 1, 1904, Universal Time, of the last calibration date of the device

properties.name: NI.FIU.Calibration.ExpirationDate
properties.description-en: Time, in seconds elapsed since 12:00 a.m., Friday, January 1, 1904, Universal Time, of the next recommended calibration date of the device

properties.name: NI.FIU.BoardFault.OvercurrentOnBusA
properties.description-en: True when Bus A exceeds the Bus High Current Limit for longer than its delay time

properties.name: NI.FIU.BoardFault.OvercurrentOnBusB
properties.description-en: True when Bus B exceeds the Bus High Current Limit for longer than its delay time

properties.name: NI.FIU.BoardFault.OvercurrentHigh
properties.description-en: Starting with the LSB, each bit represents a DUT channel, true when that DUT channel exceeds the DUT High Current Limit for longer than its delay time

properties.name: NI.FIU.BoardFault.OvercurrentLow
properties.description-en: Starting with the LSB, each bit represents a DUT channel, true when that DUT channel exceeds the DUT Low Current Limit for longer than its delay time

properties.name: NI.FIU.BoardFault.OverTemperatureOnChannelToChannel
properties.description-en: Starting with the LSB, each bit represents a channel pair, true when that channel pair's analog temperature sensor exceeds the high temperature analog transition range

properties.name: NI.FIU.BoardFault.OverTemperatureOnChannel
properties.description-en: Starting with the LSB, each bit represents a channel, true when that channel's analog temperature sensors exceed the high temperature analog transition range

properties.name: NI.FIU.BoardFault.BoardOverTemperature
properties.description-en: Starting with the LSB, each bit represents one of the board's 4 quadrant digital temperature sensors, true when that sensor exceed the high temperature digital set point

commands.name: NI.FIU.Update
commands.description-en: Executing this command allows the channel to change to the preset values.

properties.name: NI.FIU.Preset.BusSource
properties.description-en: Allows pre-setting channel 0 connectivity to Bus A, Bus B or none. An Update command is required for the change to take place.
properties.documentation-en: Enumeration: 0:'NoBus': Channel is not connected to any Bus, 1:'BusA': Channel is connected to Bus A, 2:'BusB': Channel is connected to Bus B

properties.name: NI.FIU.Preset.Load
properties.description-en: Allows pre-setting channel 0 connectivity to its load. An Update command is required for the change to take place.
properties.documentation-en: 0:'NoLoad': Channel is not connected to its Load, 1:'Load': Channel is connected to its Load
